We were hooked on the first #latch 🥹🥰

I had no clue in #2019 with Sarai (slide #1) that this would be our position for 14 months. (Whew! What a journey lol)

And in #2021 (slide #2) the first latch with my son Micah was sweet proof that God gave me the gift of being able to nurse my baby, again 🥹🙌🏽

Then in #2022, my baby boy MJ (slide #3) latched on for his first time. And here I was, experiencing God’s grace again. 

Whether you get to latch once or a thousand times, it’s a gift. I’m grateful to have experienced this special time with my babies. I will cherish it forever!❤️ 

Happy #BlackBreastfeedingWeek ✨

*SWIPE* How Do You Get Comfortable In Your Real Skin? 
👇🏽
1. You’ve got to accept what is. 
👇🏽
2. You’ve got to decide what is in your power to change.
👇🏽
3. You’ve got to recognize what is not in your power to change. 
👇🏽
4. You’ve got to embrace the transition from who you were, to who you are becoming. With joy.
👇🏽
Keyphrase: WITH JOY.
🦋
Then, no matter what your real skin looks like - you’ll love it. 🫶🏽

They either tell you how hard being a #mom is or it “looks” easier for them…

I wish I could go back and be a mama-friend to myself after having my last two lol

I wish I could have just grabbed myself by the shoulders, looking straight into my eyes, and say:

“You don’t need to be a perfect mom. You do not need to do everything right. You’re growing and learning alongside this/these children and if you let them, they will help you feel again, too.”

#Motherhood reactivated my emotions. It opened up old wounds that needed healing. What a beautiful way to heal with a little human/s there to hug, kiss, and love you for just being you 🩷 

If your kids helped you heal, drop a “✨🩷” down below!

When I first became a mom, I honestly thought I had it in the bag lol ehhhhhhhhh….

I was confident until the hard moments started rolling in. When the baby wouldn’t go to sleep after I tried everything. When I didn’t know what kind of “rock” she liked yet. When I was so impatient when putting her to sleep because I had “stuff to do”. 

#motherhood will help you (whether you like it or not lol) to reprioritize your whole life and what you want moving forward. Becoming a mom does change everything - for your good! If you allow ❤️

Allowing #motherhood to change you for the better doesn’t always look cute. There’s a lot of tears. A lot of heartache. Yet, there’s so much love to fill in the gaps. So much hope for the future in your baby’s eyes and smiles. 

They make you think “Maybe I am important to someone - maybe I am supposed to be something more than I used to believe. Maybe, I want something different now.”

🦋

#momlife #momlifebelike #momof4 #momof3 #mommy #mommylife #family #familygoals

It’s okay if you need some space to breathe, sis. 

There’s always a million things to do, catch up on, and plan for. So many expectations to show up to and this time of year especially, can feel like you’re running on fumes. 

Take a step back where you need to, not where you want to. Sometimes we want to do all the things but it just ain’t worth the cost - our sanity, our peace, our joy. 

I’m giving myself permission to not show up in all the ways I “want” to in this season. Being okay with that is hard but I’m settling into it.

Give yourself the space to decide what’s necessary, and what’s not 💕

“If you can’t accept yourself here, you won’t accept yourself there”

God has really been challenging me to see myself as He sees me, no matter what my outer appearance looks like. 

I feel like growing my hair back out is a journey towards acceptance. Whether my hair is long or short, the “ugly length” or the “it’s finally past my shoulders again!!” point. 

I think many of us have a tendency to “delay” our appreciation and acceptance of our physical appearances. Whether it’s trying to lose weight, or getting better skin, there’s a level of discomfort and dissatisfaction for ourselves along the way. 

I asked God “Why am I like this?! Why do I always feeling like I’m chasing a “better” version of me, to the point where I never feel like I can be satisfied with where I am?”

And He made something very clear….

“You don’t just “start” seeing yourself like I do, you have to renew your mind and embrace a heart made whole by Me. So that your thoughts and desires align with mine. That takes time, and if you let me - I’ll walk with you on that journey. We’ll do it together”
💕

While we may be able to hug and kiss our family in peace, there are so many around the world who can’t. 

Let’s remember them and send love their way. The world is dark in so many places - yet there is a way to spread light without having to be in those dark places ourselves. There is Someone who can send love & light into the crevices of death - because He defeated it. 🙌🏽

Our power is in the ability to love others despite our differences, mistakes or misfortunes. 

It’s a radical decision to believe that even the unloveable, can be loved. 

If you feel or have ever felt unworthy, I want to remind you that you ARE. You are worthy to be loved, cared for, and appreciated. Don’t let people force you into believing that you don’t “deserve.”

God, who IS love, believes you’re worth it. At your highest AND YOUR LOWEST. Let’s be people who not only experience this, but who publicly bear fruit of it. This way, no one will mistake who we belong to and who we are so loved by 💕

Believe it.

A love letter to #parents 💕  Whether you have little ones like us or your kids are grown - the feeling of “defeat” seems to a common thread. One that maybe we shouldn’t be trying to avoid, but trying to get better at going through, getting over, and moving on from. 

While I have many years of #motherhood ahead of me, this idea of not allowing the feeling of “defeat” to throw me off my post as a mother, and wife, will be one  I always work towards. Especially when I know, the one who is IN ME is working nonstop to not just supply my needs, but the needs of my family, too. ✨🙌🏽💕
Y’all started this and I’m gone run with it 😂🥰

It’s Official - Her Name Is “Claire” 😂 

I’m actually starting to embrace that roller sets may be the hairstyle of my “mom” era ✨ I can’t wait to see how it continues to look as my hair grows out even more!! 

Quick Answers To Questions Yall Have Been Asking! 

1. My hair is about 80% natural, my tips still have a bit of a texturizer on them from when I had my pixie cut! 

2. I use LOTS of water and @influancehaircare styling foam to set my rollers.

3. I use rollers that have little ridges/teeth that help grip and create tension on my hair. I have been searching for them to link but I got them from a random website years ago that was selling Dominican Hair Rollers and pins. I’ll keep looking for y’all, tho! Alternatively, you can use magnetic rollers too. 

4. I sit under a hooded dryer to set these rollers for about 30-45 min. Then, I brush it out and wrap it for 10-30 min to give it a smoother look & lock in shine. 

Are you here for a roller set era or what?!

Let’s do the fluffiest roller set on the planet ✨😘 It’s funny how simple this process is compared to everything else we do to our hair today 😂 anyway; here’s the hair tutorial yall didn’t know you needed until now! 💕 

Products used are tagged in my stories & LTK shop! @JadeGodbolt

And I share everything I learn because the mamas & the girlies DESERVE! 🙌🏽 Also, in this economy?! Yeah - DIY me sis 😂💕 

(No shade though, if I could be in somebody’s salon on a weekly basis - that would be beautiful! But you know - it’s okay to go through seasons where you gotta figure it out on your own. Sometimes, it just makes more sense time & resource wise.)

My #beautyroutine has gone through so many ups and downs since becoming a mom lol 

#STAGE1 Pre-Kids: I’d carve out AT LEAST 3 hours to do hair & makeup because it was going to be a full glam situation 9 times out of 10 lol

#STAGE2 Postpartum: WHAT DO YOU MEAN, TAKE A SHOWER?! I DON’T HAVE TIME TO THINK about makeup/hair when I’m trying to figure out how to raise a human being!!! 

#STAGE3 Post-Postpartum: Oh wait, I can breathe again lol but wait…I don’t even know what I like anymore. And I’ve got 30- 45 min MAX for makeup before I’ve gotta grab the baby. No plan for hair (😩)

#STAGE4 Mom of Multiple Kids: Okay look - as long as I can wear the youngest, give the other one a snack and their favorite toy, and keep the other one occupied near me - I’ve got 30-45 minutes to get this done and WE GONE GET IT DONE! 

A lot can change over a few years 😂 But what mamas always gone do, is EVENTUALLY figure it out! If you’re a mom, what stage are you in?!
